{"lemma":"سَنَدٌ","slug":"سَنَدٌ","root":"س.ن.د","root_slug":"س-ن-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ن-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20922"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lean, to rest, to support oneself"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ascend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be near, to be close to, to approach"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to support firmly, to prop up (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"advocacy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"support"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"improvement, reinforcement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a surface that rises from a base, face of a mountain, a wall"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a support, a thing which one leans upon, to recline against"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a support, a thing which one leans upon, to recline against; a cushion or pillow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a thing or person which one can rely on, a thing sturdy or not liable to move"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"backing, a means of being held up or supported"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"backing, a means of being held up or supported; the support for a hadith's validity; the chain of narrators on which its veracity rests"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20922","headword_ar":"سَنَدٌ","root":"snd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that faces one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a mountain,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rises from"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean","text_ar":"عَن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safoH","text_ar":"سَفْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acclivity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising part, in the face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"front,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a mountain or a valley: (T, M, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated, portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of ground: (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonaAdN","text_ar":"اَسْنَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A,) [properly a pl. of pauc., but] the only pl. form. (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing, such as a wall &c., against,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, which one leans, rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stays himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misonadN","text_ar":"مِسْنَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musonadN","text_ar":"مُسْنَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter in the TA said to be with fet-h, but this is evidently a mistake, occasioned by a copyist's writing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wyftH","text_ar":"ويفتح"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wyDm~","text_ar":"ويضمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signify [the same,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing against,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, which one leans, rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stays himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and the former of these two particularly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cushion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and more particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large cushion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillow, against which one leans;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. by Golius on the authority of Meyd;] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAnidu","text_ar":"مَسَانِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, Msb.) ―         -b3-  Applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotamadN","text_ar":"مُعْتَمَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A person upon whom one leans, rests, stays himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relies"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) a man's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotamad","text_ar":"مُعْتَمَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stay, support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of reliance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotanadN","text_ar":"مُسْتَنَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanadN","text_ar":"سَنَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, upon whom people lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwasanadiY","text_ar":"هُوَسَنَدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotanadiY","text_ar":"مُسْتَنَدِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is my stay, support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object of reliance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN qawiY~u Als~anadi","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ قَوِىُّ السَّنَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tradition valid in respect of the authority upon which it rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which it is traced up"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isonaAdN","text_ar":"اـِسْنَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musonadN","text_ar":"مُسْنَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of ElYemen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonaAdN","text_ar":"اَسْنَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the pl. is like the sing.: (IAar, K:) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaAbN sanadN","text_ar":"اَثْوَابٌ سَنَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanad","text_ar":"سَنَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA, from a trad.:) Ibn-Buzurj says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~anadu","text_ar":"السَّنَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asonaAdu mina Alv~iyaAbi","text_ar":"الاَسْنَادُ مِنَ الثِّيَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of those called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he cites, from a poet, the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~apu","text_ar":"جُبَّةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asonaAdK","text_ar":"اَسْنَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, he says, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a red jubbeh of those"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Accord. to Lth, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of clothing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shirt with a shirt over it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short shirts made of pieces of cloth, one whereof is concealed beneath another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whatever appears ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u maA Zahara","text_ar":"كُلُّ مَا ظَهَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") thereof is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoTN","text_ar":"سِمْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (O:) [this app. explains the meaning of what here follows:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~anadu","text_ar":"السَّنَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [a term used in the case of] thy wearing a long shirt beneath a shirt shorter than it. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","A","Mgh","Msb","IAar","K","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}